## stdout-path

**Value type:** `<string>`

A string that specifies the full path to the node representing the device to be used for boot console output. If the character ":" is present in the value it terminates the path. The value may be an alias. If the `stdin-path` property is not specified, `stdout-path` should be assumed to define the input device as well.

Note: Older versions of devicetrees may contain a deprecated form of this property called `linux,stdout-path`. The meaning and use of the two properties is identical.

```dts
/* arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8550-qrd.dts */
chosen {
    stdout-path = "serial0:115200n8";
};
```
